Description: Estate planning attorney
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: At Rocky Mountain Wills and Trusts we understand the value of planning ahead. Most people go through life planning all the time. They plan their vacations, their weekends, they set into motions plans for how the new year is going to go. But not enough people think about estate planning, that type of planning that doesn’t just look ahead to what’s next but instead it plans for how everything will end. It takes time, energy, understanding, and a willingness to consider the morbid possibility of a world without us in it, to properly plan an estate. This is a lot to invest in something, but Rocky Mountain Wills and Trusts knows that investment pays off. Estate planning isn’t only about planning for the end but that is a key element. That’s why we offer help selecting your power of attorney and drafting your will to ensure that your desires are followed after you pass. But estate planning doesn’t necessarily mean that you’re only planning for a future without you. One way that estate planning can help you in the present is through a focus on asset protection. Asset protection refers to a number of different tactics that can be used to ensure that your assets aren’t liable should you find yourself on the wrong side of a lawsuit. Asset protection can also be useful when it comes to those that inherit said assets after you pass. One way that we protect assets is by creating a trust in which assets can be transferred into for protection. There are a number of different types of trusts and picking the right one for your specific needs is a matter of comparing them. Save yourself some time and a headache by working with Rocky Mountain Wills and Trusts and letting one of our talented attorneys help you plan your estate and protect your assets.

Many are finding out that Social Security is not as secure as they would like it. They may need to work longer or work until the die in order to survive. Not very many people are talking about leaving their job even after retirement age. One of the reasons is because   of the lack of money. Also we have found that those who are looking to retire hesitate because they are not sure what they will do once leave their job or their career ends. They are not sure what’s next?  Many have been in their job or career for many decades and have developed quite an emotional connection to their job and the people they are connected with at the job. Think about it. We spend 80% of our week working and 80% of entire life working for a Company or Corporation.    Our focus in 2010 was to help improve our economy by helping those who make biggest difference in our economy “the average every day worker”. Out of the many people we have contacted we have found that , about 60%, would at least take a look at a way for them to make some additional income without a second job. The work comes in for us when we share about our products and services. We have found that most only know one way to make money and that is through Linear Income , a job.  We share with them they can create other types income besides Linear Income. We share with them at the right time about “Leveraged Income, Royalty Income and Residual Income”. If they are receptive to that we share with them what our products and services are and how they can benefit with our help and support.
